  "text": "To characterize the PMT working regimes, we assume infinite sampling rate and zero noise variance of the PMT detector, which does not depend on the sampling rate and can be regarded as the fundamental characterization. Then, the probability mass function (PMF) of the detected photons number N can be characterized by the following result [CITATION_1] . Note that in such a scenario, the photons arrived within duration τ of an arrived photon cannot be detected, which accords with the basic assumption of work [CITATION_2] .",
