  "bib_entries": {
    "122438830": {
      "title": "Dead-time effects in photon counting distributions",
      "abstract": "Abstract The photon counting distribution was obtained taking into account the dead time of the counting system. For our own experimental motivation, we deal with a dead time of the paralyzable type and an “equilibrium” process with regard to the start of the sampling time. The formula is exact provided that the distribution of the incident photon is Poissonian. In addition, the characteristic function of the distribution is presented and the first few moments are derived from it."
    }
